data.def: Diagnose, adjust, repair, or overhaul small engines used to power lawn mowers, chain saws, recreational sporting equipment, and related equipment.

data.title: Miscellaneous vehicle and mobile equipment mechanics, installers, etc
data.soc_title: Miscellaneous Vehicle and Mobile Equipment Mechanics, Installers, and Repairers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Bicycle repairers
data.def: Repair and service bicycles.

data.title: Recreational vehicle service technicians
data.def: Diagnose, inspect, adjust, repair, or overhaul recreational vehicles including travel trailers. May specialize in maintaining gas, electrical, hydraulic, plumbing, or chassis/towing systems as well as repairing generators, appliances, and interior components. Includes workers who perform customized van conversions. Excludes “Automotive Service Technicians and Mechanics” (49-3023) and “Bus and Truck Mechanics and Diesel Engine Specialists” (49-3031) who also work on recreation vehicles.

data.title: Tire repairers and changers
data.def: Repair and replace tires.

data.title: Other installation, maintenance, etc
data.soc_title: Other Installation, Maintenance, and Repair Occupations
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Control and valve installers and repairers
data.soc_title: Control and Valve Installers and Repairers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Mechanical door repairers
data.def: Install, service, or repair automatic door mechanisms and hydraulic doors. Includes garage door mechanics.

data.title: Control and valve installers and repairers, except mechanical door
data.soc_title: Control and Valve Installers and Repairers, Except Mechanical Door
data.def: Install, repair, and maintain mechanical regulating and controlling devices, such as electric meters, gas regulators, thermostats, safety and flow valves, and other mechanical governors.

data.title: Heating, air conditioning, etc
data.soc_title: Heating, Air Conditioning, and Refrigeration Mechanics and Installers
data.def: Install or repair heating, central air conditioning, HVAC, or refrigeration systems, including oil burners, hot-air furnaces, and heating stoves.

data.title: Home appliance repairers
data.def: Repair, adjust, or install all types of electric or gas household appliances, such as refrigerators, washers, dryers, and ovens.

data.title: Industrial machinery installation, repair, etc
data.soc_title: Industrial Machinery Installation, Repair, and Maintenance Workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Industrial machinery mechanics
data.def: Repair, install, adjust, or maintain industrial production and processing machinery or refinery and pipeline distribution systems. May also install, dismantle, or move machinery and heavy equipment according to plans. Excludes “Mobile Heavy Equipment Mechanics, Except Engines” (49-3042), and “Maintenance Workers, Machinery” (49-9043).

data.title: Maintenance workers, machinery
data.def: Lubricate machinery, change parts, or perform other routine machinery maintenance. Excludes “Maintenance and Repair Workers, General” (49-9071).

data.title: Millwrights
data.def: Install, dismantle, or move machinery and heavy equipment according to layout plans, blueprints, or other drawings.

data.title: Refractory materials repairers, except brickmasons
data.def: Build or repair equipment such as furnaces, kilns, cupolas, boilers, converters, ladles, soaking pits, and ovens, using refractory materials.

data.title: Line installers and repairers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Electrical power-line installers and repairers
data.def: Install or repair cables or wires used in electrical power or distribution systems. May erect poles and light or heavy duty transmission towers. Excludes “Electrical and Electronics Repairers, Powerhouse, Substation, and Relay” (49-2095).

data.title: Telecommunications line installers and repairers
data.def: Install and repair telecommunications cable, including fiber optics.

data.title: Precision instrument and equipment repairers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Camera and photographic equipment repairers
data.def: Repair and adjust cameras and photographic equipment, including commercial video and motion picture camera equipment.

data.title: Medical equipment repairers
data.def: Test, adjust, or repair biomedical or electromedical equipment.

data.title: Musical instrument repairers and tuners
data.def: Repair percussion, stringed, reed, or wind instruments. May specialize in one area, such as piano tuning. Excludes “Audiovisual Equipment Installers and Repairers" (49-2097) who repair electrical and electronic musical instruments.

data.title: Watch and clock repairers
data.def: Repair, clean, and adjust mechanisms of timing instruments, such as watches and clocks. Includes watchmakers, watch technicians, and mechanical timepiece repairers. Excludes "Timing Device Assemblers and Adjusters” (51-2061).

data.title: Precision instrument and equipment repairers, all other
data.soc_title: Precision Instrument and Equipment Repairers, All Other
data.def: All precision instrument and equipment repairers not listed separately.

data.title: Maintenance and repair workers, general
data.def: Perform work involving the skills of two or more maintenance or craft occupations to keep machines, mechanical equipment, or the structure of a building in repair. Duties may involve pipe fitting; HVAC maintenance; insulating; welding; machining; carpentry; repairing electrical or mechanical equipment; installing, aligning, and balancing new equipment; and repairing buildings, floors, or stairs. Excludes “Facilities Managers” (11-3013) and “Maintenance Workers, Machinery” (49-9043).

data.title: Wind turbine service technicians
data.def: Inspect, diagnose, adjust, or repair wind turbines. Perform maintenance on wind turbine equipment including resolving electrical, mechanical, and hydraulic malfunctions.

data.title: Miscellaneous installation, maintenance, etc
data.soc_title: Miscellaneous Installation, Maintenance, and Repair Workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Coin, vending, etc
data.soc_title: Coin, Vending, and Amusement Machine Servicers and Repairers
data.def: Install, service, adjust, or repair coin, vending, or amusement machines including video games, juke boxes, pinball machines, or slot machines.

data.title: Commercial divers
data.def: Work below surface of water, using surface-supplied air or scuba equipment to inspect, repair, remove, or install equipment and structures. May use a variety of power and hand tools, such as drills, sledgehammers, torches, and welding equipment. May conduct tests or experiments, rig explosives, or photograph structures or marine life. Excludes “Athletes and Sports Competitors” (27-2021), “Police and Sheriff’s Patrol Officers” (33-3051), and “Fishing and Hunting Workers” (45-3031).

data.title: Locksmiths and safe repairers
data.def: Repair and open locks, make keys, change locks and safe combinations, and install and repair safes.

data.title: Manufactured building and mobile home installers
data.soc_title: Manufactured Building and Mobile Home Installers
data.def: Move or install mobile homes or prefabricated buildings.

data.title: Riggers
data.def: Set up or repair rigging for construction projects, manufacturing plants, logging yards, ships and shipyards, or for the entertainment industry.

data.title: Signal and track switch repairers
data.def: Install, inspect, test, maintain, or repair electric gate crossings, signals, signal equipment, track switches, section lines, or intercommunications systems within a railroad system.

data.title: Helpers--installation, maintenance, etc
data.def: Help installation, maintenance, and repair workers in maintenance, parts replacement, and repair of vehicles, industrial machinery, and electrical and electronic equipment. Perform duties such as furnishing tools, materials, and supplies to other workers; cleaning work area, machines, and tools; and holding materials or tools for other workers.

data.title: Installation, maintenance, etc
data.soc_title: Installation, Maintenance, and Repair Workers, All Other
data.def: All installation, maintenance, and repair workers not listed separately.

data.title: Production jobs
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Supervisors of production workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: First-line supervisors of production and operating workers
data.soc_title: First-Line Supervisors of Production and Operating Workers
data.def: Directly supervise and coordinate the activities of production and operating workers, such as inspectors, precision workers, machine setters and operators, assemblers, fabricators, and plant and system operators. Excludes team or work leaders.

data.title: Assemblers and fabricators
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Aircraft structure, surfaces, etc
data.soc_title: Aircraft Structure, Surfaces, Rigging, and Systems Assemblers
data.def: Assemble, fit, fasten, and install parts of airplanes, space vehicles, or missiles, such as tails, wings, fuselage, bulkheads, stabilizers, landing gear, rigging and control equipment, or heating and ventilating systems.

data.title: Electrical, electronics, etc
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Coil winders, tapers, etc
data.def: Wind wire coils used in electrical components, such as resistors and transformers, and in electrical equipment and instruments, such as field cores, bobbins, armature cores, electrical motors, generators, and control equipment.

data.title: Electrical, electronic, etc
data.def: No job definition found.

data.title: Engine and other machine assemblers
data.def: Construct, assemble, or rebuild machines, such as engines, turbines, and similar equipment used in such industries as construction, extraction, textiles, and paper manufacturing.

data.title: Structural metal fabricators and fitters
data.def: Fabricate, position, align, and fit parts of structural metal products. Shipfitters are included in “Layout Workers, Metal and Plastic” (51-4192).

data.title: Fiberglass laminators and fabricators
data.def: Laminate layers of fiberglass on molds to form boat decks and hulls, bodies for golf carts, automobiles, or other products.

data.title: Timing device assemblers and adjusters
data.def: Perform precision assembling or adjusting, within narrow tolerances, of timing devices such as digital clocks or timing devices with electrical or electronic components. Watchmakers are included in “Watch and Clock Repairers” (49-9064).

data.title: Miscellaneous assemblers and fabricators
data.def: No job definition found.

data.title: Food processing workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Bakers
data.def: Mix and bake ingredients to produce breads, rolls, cookies, cakes, pies, pastries, or other baked goods. Pastry chefs in restaurants and hotels are included with “Chefs and Head Cooks” (35-1011).

data.title: Butchers and other meat, poultry, etc
data.soc_title: Butchers and Other Meat, Poultry, and Fish Processing Workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Butchers and meat cutters
data.def: Cut, trim, or prepare consumer-sized portions of meat for use or sale in retail establishments.

data.title: Meat, poultry, etc
data.soc_title: Meat, Poultry, and Fish Cutters and Trimmers
data.def: Use hands or hand tools to perform routine cutting and trimming of meat, poultry, and seafood.

data.title: Slaughterers and meat packers
data.def: Perform nonroutine or precision functions involving the preparation of large portions of meat. Work may include specialized slaughtering tasks, cutting standard or premium cuts of meat for marketing, making sausage, or wrapping meats. Work typically occurs in slaughtering, meat packing, or wholesale establishments. Excludes “Meat, Poultry, and Fish Cutters and Trimmers” (51-3022) who perform routine meat cutting.

data.title: Miscellaneous food processing workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Food and tobacco roasting, baking, etc
data.soc_title: Food and Tobacco Roasting, Baking, and Drying Machine Operators and Tenders
data.def: Operate or tend food or tobacco roasting, baking, or drying equipment, including hearth ovens, kiln driers, roasters, char kilns, and vacuum drying equipment.

data.title: Food batchmakers
data.def: Set up and operate equipment that mixes or blends ingredients used in the manufacturing of food products. Includes candy makers and cheese makers.

data.title: Food cooking machine operators and tenders
data.soc_title: Food Cooking Machine Operators and Tenders
data.def: Operate or tend cooking equipment, such as steam cooking vats, deep fry cookers, pressure cookers, kettles, and boilers, to prepare food products. Excludes “Food and Tobacco Roasting, Baking, and Drying Machine Operators and Tenders” (51-3091).

data.title: Food processing workers, all other
data.def: All food processing workers not listed separately

data.title: Metal workers and plastic workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Forming machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Forming Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Extruding and drawing machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Extruding and Drawing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend machines to extrude or draw thermoplastic or metal materials into tubes, rods, hoses, wire, bars, or structural shapes.

data.title: Forging machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Forging Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend forging machines to taper, shape, or form metal or plastic parts.

data.title: Rolling machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Rolling Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend machines to roll steel or plastic forming bends, beads, knurls, rolls, or plate, or to flatten, temper, or reduce gauge of material.

data.title: Machine tool cutting setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Machine Tool Cutting Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Cutting, punching, etc
data.soc_title: Cutting, Punching, and Press Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend machines to saw, cut, shear, slit, punch, crimp, notch, bend, or straighten metal or plastic material.

data.title: Drilling and boring machine tool setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Drilling and Boring Machine Tool Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend drilling machines to drill, bore, ream, mill, or countersink metal or plastic work pieces.

data.title: Grinding, lapping, etc
data.soc_title: Grinding, Lapping, Polishing, and Buffing Machine Tool Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend grinding and related tools that remove excess material or burrs from surfaces, sharpen edges or corners, or buff, hone, or polish metal or plastic work pieces.

data.title: Lathe and turning machine tool setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Lathe and Turning Machine Tool Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend lathe and turning machines to turn, bore, thread, form, or face metal or plastic materials, such as wire, rod, or bar stock.

data.title: Milling and planing machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Milling and Planing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend milling or planing machines to mill, plane, shape, groove, or profile metal or plastic work pieces.

data.title: Machinists
data.def: Set up and operate a variety of machine tools to produce precision parts and instruments out of metal. Includes precision instrument makers who fabricate, modify, or repair mechanical instruments. May also fabricate and modify parts to make or repair machine tools or maintain industrial machines, applying knowledge of mechanics, mathematics, metal properties, layout, and machining procedures. Machinists who primarily program or operate computer numerically controlled (CNC) equipment are classified in “Computer Numerically Controlled Tool Operators and Programmers” (51-9160).

data.title: Metal furnace operators, tenders, etc
data.soc_title: Metal Furnace Operators, Tenders, Pourers, and Casters
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Metal-refining furnace operators and tenders
data.def: Operate or tend furnaces, such as gas, oil, coal, electric-arc or electric induction, open-hearth, or oxygen furnaces, to melt and refine metal before casting or to produce specified types of steel. Excludes “Heat Treating Equipment Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic” (51-4191).

data.title: Pourers and casters, metal
data.def: Operate hand-controlled mechanisms to pour and regulate the flow of molten metal into molds to produce castings or ingots.

data.title: Model makers and patternmakers, metal and plastic
data.soc_title: Model Makers and Patternmakers, Metal and Plastic
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Model makers, metal and plastic
data.def: Set up and operate machines, such as lathes, milling and engraving machines, and jig borers to make working models of metal or plastic objects. Includes template makers.

data.title: Patternmakers, metal and plastic
data.def: Lay out, machine, fit, and assemble castings and parts to metal or plastic foundry patterns, core boxes, or match plates.

data.title: Molders and molding machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Molders and Molding Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Foundry mold and coremakers
data.def: Make or form wax or sand cores or molds used in the production of metal castings in foundries. Excludes “Molding, Coremaking, and Casting Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic” (51-4072) and “Molders, Shapers, and Casters, Except Metal and Plastic” (51-9195).

data.title: Molding, coremaking, etc
data.soc_title: Molding, Coremaking, and Casting Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend metal or plastic molding, casting, or coremaking machines to mold or cast metal or thermoplastic parts or products.

data.title: Multiple machine tool setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Multiple Machine Tool Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend more than one type of cutting or forming machine tool or robot.

data.title: Tool and die makers
data.def: Analyze specifications, lay out metal stock, set up and operate machine tools, and fit and assemble parts to make and repair dies, cutting tools, jigs, fixtures, gauges, and machinists’ hand tools.

data.title: Welding, soldering, etc
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Welders, cutters, etc
data.def: Use hand-welding, flame-cutting, hand-soldering, or brazing equipment to weld or join metal components or to fill holes, indentations, or seams of fabricated metal products.

data.title: Welding, soldering, etc
data.soc_title: Welding, Soldering, and Brazing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend welding, soldering, or brazing machines or robots that weld, braze, solder, or heat treat metal products, components, or assemblies. Includes workers who operate laser cutters or laser-beam machines.

data.title: Miscellaneous metal workers and plastic workers
data.soc_title: Miscellaneous Metal Workers and Plastic Workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Heat treating equipment setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Heat Treating Equipment Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend heating equipment, such as heat-treating furnaces, flame-hardening machines, induction machines, soaking pits, or vacuum equipment to temper, harden, anneal, or heat treat metal or plastic objects.

data.title: Layout workers, metal and plastic
data.def: Lay out reference points and dimensions on metal or plastic stock or workpieces, such as sheets, plates, tubes, structural shapes, castings, or machine parts, for further processing. Includes shipfitters.

data.title: Plating machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Plating Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend plating machines to coat metal or plastic products with chromium, zinc, copper, cadmium, nickel, or other metal to protect or decorate surfaces. Typically, the product being coated is immersed in molten metal or an electrolytic solution. Excludes “Coating, Painting, and Spraying Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders” (51-9124).

data.title: Tool grinders, filers, etc
data.def: Perform precision smoothing, sharpening, polishing, or grinding of metal objects.

data.title: Metal workers and plastic workers, all other
data.soc_title: Metal Workers and Plastic Workers, All Other
data.def: All metal workers and plastic workers not listed separately.

data.title: Printing workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Prepress technicians and workers
data.def: Format and proof text and images submitted by designers and clients into finished pages that can be printed. Includes digital and photo typesetting. May produce printing plates.

data.title: Printing press operators
data.def: Set up and operate digital, letterpress, lithographic, flexographic, gravure, or other printing machines. Includes short-run offset printing presses.

data.title: Print binding and finishing workers
data.def: Bind books and other publications or finish printed products by hand or machine. May set up binding and finishing machines.

data.title: Textile, apparel, etc
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Laundry and dry-cleaning workers
data.def: Operate or tend washing or dry-cleaning machines to wash or dry-clean industrial or household articles, such as cloth garments, suede, leather, furs, blankets, draperies, linens, rugs, and carpets. Includes spotters and dyers of these articles.

data.title: Pressers, textile, etc
data.soc_title: Pressers, Textile, Garment, and Related Materials
data.def: Press or shape articles by hand or machine.

data.title: Sewing machine operators
data.def: Operate or tend sewing machines to join, reinforce, decorate, or perform related sewing operations in the manufacture of garment or nongarment products.

data.title: Shoe and leather workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Shoe and leather workers and repairers
data.soc_title: Shoe and Leather Workers and Repairers
data.def: Construct, decorate, or repair leather and leather-like products, such as luggage, shoes, and saddles. May use hand tools.

data.title: Shoe machine operators and tenders
data.def: Operate or tend a variety of machines to join, decorate, reinforce, or finish shoes and shoe parts.

data.title: Tailors, dressmakers, etc
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Sewers, hand
data.def: Sew, join, reinforce, or finish, usually with needle and thread, a variety of manufactured items. Includes weavers and stitchers.

data.title: Tailors, dressmakers, etc
data.def: Design, make, alter, repair, or fit garments.

data.title: Textile machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Textile Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Textile bleaching and dyeing machine operators and tenders
data.soc_title: Textile Bleaching and Dyeing Machine Operators and Tenders
data.def: Operate or tend machines to bleach, shrink, wash, dye, or finish textiles or synthetic or glass fibers.

data.title: Textile cutting machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Textile Cutting Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend machines that cut textiles.

data.title: Textile knitting and weaving machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Textile Knitting and Weaving Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend machines that knit, loop, weave, or draw in textiles. Excludes “Sewing Machine Operators” (51-6031).

data.title: Textile winding, twisting, etc
data.soc_title: Textile Winding, Twisting, and Drawing Out Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend machines that wind or twist textiles; or draw out and combine sliver, such as wool, hemp, or synthetic fibers. Includes slubber machine and drawing frame operators.

data.title: Miscellaneous textile, apparel, etc
data.soc_title: Miscellaneous Textile, Apparel, and Furnishings Workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Extruding and forming machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Extruding and Forming Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Synthetic and Glass Fibers
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend machines that extrude and form continuous filaments from synthetic materials, such as liquid polymer, rayon, and fiberglass.

data.title: Fabric and apparel patternmakers
data.def: Draw and construct sets of precision master fabric patterns or layouts. May also mark and cut fabrics and apparel.

data.title: Upholsterers
data.def: Make, repair, or replace upholstery for household furniture or transportation vehicles.

data.title: Textile, apparel, etc
data.soc_title: Textile, Apparel, and Furnishings Workers, All Other
data.def: All textile, apparel, and furnishings workers not listed separately.

data.title: Woodworkers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Cabinetmakers and bench carpenters
data.def: Cut, shape, and assemble wooden articles or set up and operate a variety of woodworking machines, such as power saws, jointers, and mortisers to surface, cut, or shape lumber or to fabricate parts for wood products. Excludes “Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders” (51-7040).

data.title: Furniture finishers
data.def: Shape, finish, and refinish damaged, worn, or used furniture or new high-grade furniture to specified color or finish.

data.title: Model makers and patternmakers, wood
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Model makers, wood
data.def: Construct full-size and scale wooden precision models of products. Includes wood jig builders and loft workers.

data.title: Patternmakers, wood
data.def: Plan, lay out, and construct wooden unit or sectional patterns used in forming sand molds for castings.

data.title: Woodworking machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Sawing machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Sawing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Wood
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend wood sawing machines. May operate computer numerically controlled (CNC) equipment. Includes lead sawyers. Workers who primarily program or operate CNC equipment are classified in “Computer Numerically Controlled Tool Operators and Programmers” (51-9160).

data.title: Woodworking machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Except Sawing
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend woodworking machines, such as drill presses, lathes, shapers, routers, sanders, planers, and wood nailing machines. May operate computer numerically controlled (CNC) equipment. Workers who primarily program or operate CNC equipment are classified in “Computer Numerically Controlled Tool Operators and Programmers” (51-9160).

data.title: Woodworkers, all other
data.def: All woodworkers not listed separately.

data.title: Plant and system operators
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Power plant operators, distributors, etc
data.soc_title: Power Plant Operators, Distributors, and Dispatchers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Nuclear power reactor operators
data.def: Operate or control nuclear reactors. Move control rods, start and stop equipment, monitor and adjust controls, and record data in logs. Implement emergency procedures when needed. May respond to abnormalities, determine cause, and recommend corrective action.

data.title: Power distributors and dispatchers
data.def: Coordinate, regulate, or distribute electricity or steam.

data.title: Power plant operators
data.def: Control, operate, or maintain machinery to generate electric power. Includes auxiliary equipment operators. Excludes “Nuclear Power Reactor Operators” (51-8011).

data.title: Stationary engineers and boiler operators
data.def: Operate or maintain stationary engines, boilers, or other mechanical equipment to provide utilities for buildings or industrial processes. Operate equipment such as steam engines, generators, motors, turbines, and steam boilers.

data.title: Water and wastewater treatment plant and system operators
data.soc_title: Water and Wastewater Treatment Plant and System Operators
data.def: Operate or control an entire process or system of machines, often through the use of control boards, to transfer or treat water or wastewater.

data.title: Miscellaneous plant and system operators
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Chemical plant and system operators
data.def: Control or operate entire chemical processes or system of machines.

data.title: Gas plant operators
data.def: Distribute or process gas for utility companies and others by controlling compressors to maintain specified pressures on main pipelines.

data.title: Petroleum pump system operators, refinery operators, etc
data.soc_title: Petroleum Pump System Operators, Refinery Operators, and Gaugers
data.def: Operate or control petroleum refining or processing units. May specialize in controlling manifold and pumping systems, gauging or testing oil in storage tanks, or regulating the flow of oil into pipelines.

data.title: Plant and system operators, all other
data.soc_title: Plant and System Operators, All Other
data.def: All plant and system operators not listed separately.

data.title: Other production jobs
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Chemical processing machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Chemical Processing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Chemical equipment operators and tenders
data.def: Operate or tend equipment to control chemical changes or reactions in the processing of industrial or consumer products. Equipment used includes devulcanizers, steam-jacketed kettles, and reactor vessels. Excludes “Chemical Plant and System Operators” (51-8091).

data.title: Separating, filtering, etc
data.soc_title: Separating, Filtering, Clarifying, Precipitating, and Still Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend continuous flow or vat-type equipment; filter presses; shaker screens; centrifuges; condenser tubes; precipitating, fermenting, or evaporating tanks; scrubbing towers; or batch stills. These machines extract, sort, or separate liquids, gases, or solids from other materials to recover a refined product. Includes dairy processing equipment operators. Excludes “Chemical Equipment Operators and Tenders” (51-9011).

data.title: Crushing, grinding, etc
data.soc_title: Crushing, Grinding, Polishing, Mixing, and Blending Workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Crushing, grinding, etc
data.soc_title: Crushing, Grinding, and Polishing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend machines to crush, grind, or polish materials, such as coal, glass, grain, stone, food, or rubber.

data.title: Grinding and polishing workers, hand
data.def: Grind, sand, or polish, using hand tools or hand-held power tools, a variety of metal, wood, stone, clay, plastic, or glass objects. Includes chippers, buffers, and finishers.

data.title: Mixing and blending machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Mixing and Blending Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend machines to mix or blend materials, such as chemicals, tobacco, liquids, color pigments, or explosive ingredients. Excludes “Food Batchmakers” (51-3092).

data.title: Cutting workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Cutters and trimmers, hand
data.def: Use hand tools or hand-held power tools to cut and trim a variety of manufactured items, such as carpet, fabric, stone, glass, or rubber.

data.title: Cutting and slicing machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Cutting and Slicing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend machines that cut or slice materials, such as glass, stone, cork, rubber, tobacco, food, paper, or insulating material. Excludes “Cutting, Punching, and Press Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic” (51-4031), “Textile Cutting Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders” (51-6062), and “Woodworking Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders” (51-7040).

data.title: Extruding, forming, etc
data.soc_title: Extruding, Forming, Pressing, and Compacting Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend machines, such as glass-forming machines, plodder machines, and tuber machines, to shape and form products such as glassware, food, rubber, soap, brick, tile, clay, wax, tobacco, or cosmetics. Excludes “Shoe Machine Operators and Tenders” (51-6042) and “Paper Goods Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders” (51-9196).

data.title: Furnace, kiln, etc
data.soc_title: Furnace, Kiln, Oven, Drier, and Kettle Operators and Tenders
data.def: Operate or tend heating equipment other than basic metal, plastic, or food processing equipment. Includes activities such as annealing glass, drying lumber, curing rubber, removing moisture from materials, or boiling soap.

data.title: Inspectors, testers, etc
data.soc_title: Inspectors, Testers, Sorters, Samplers, and Weighers
data.def: Inspect, test, sort, sample, or weigh nonagricultural raw materials or processed, machined, fabricated, or assembled parts or products for defects, wear, and deviations from specifications. May use precision measuring instruments and complex test equipment.

data.title: Jewelers and precious stone and metal workers
data.soc_title: Jewelers and Precious Stone and Metal Workers
data.def: Design, fabricate, adjust, repair, or appraise jewelry, gold, silver, other precious metals, or gems. Includes diamond polishers and gem cutters, and persons who perform precision casting and modeling of molds, casting metal in molds, or setting precious and semiprecious stones for jewelry and related products.

data.title: Dental and ophthalmic laboratory technicians and medical appliance technicians
data.soc_title: Dental and Ophthalmic Laboratory Technicians and Medical Appliance Technicians
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Dental laboratory technicians
data.def: Construct and repair full or partial dentures or dental appliances. Excludes “Dental Assistants” (31-9091).

data.title: Medical appliance technicians
data.def: Construct, maintain, or repair medical supportive devices such as braces, orthotics and prosthetic devices, joints, arch supports, and other surgical and medical appliances.

data.title: Ophthalmic laboratory technicians
data.def: Cut, grind, and polish eyeglasses, contact lenses, or other precision optical elements. Assemble and mount lenses into frames or process other optical elements. Includes precision lens polishers or grinders, centerer-edgers, and lens mounters. Excludes “Opticians, Dispensing ” (29-2081).

data.title: Packaging and filling machine operators and tenders
data.soc_title: Packaging and Filling Machine Operators and Tenders
data.def: Operate or tend machines to prepare industrial or consumer products for storage or shipment. Includes cannery workers who pack food products.

data.title: Painting workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Painting, coating, etc
data.def: Paint, coat, or decorate articles, such as furniture, glass, plateware, pottery, jewelry, toys, books, or leather. Excludes “Artists and Related Workers" (27-1010), “Designers” (27-1020), “Photographic Process Workers and Processing Machine Operators” (51-9151), and “Etchers and Engravers” (51-9194).

data.title: Coating, painting, etc
data.soc_title: Coating, Painting, and Spraying Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend spraying or rolling machines to coat or paint any of a wide variety of products, including glassware, cloth, ceramics, metal, plastic, paper, or wood, with lacquer, silver, copper, rubber, varnish, glaze, enamel, oil, or rust-proofing materials. Includes painters of transportation vehicles such as painters in auto body repair facilities. Excludes “Plating Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders, Metal and Plastic” (51-4193).

data.title: Semiconductor processing technicians
data.def: Perform any or all of the following functions in the manufacture of electronic semiconductors: load semiconductor material into furnace; saw formed ingots into segments; load individual segment into crystal growing chamber and monitor controls; locate crystal axis in ingot using x-ray equipment and saw ingots into wafers; and clean, polish, and load wafers into series of special purpose furnaces, chemical baths, and equipment used to form circuitry and change conductive properties.

data.title: Photographic process workers and processing machine operators
data.soc_title: Photographic Process Workers and Processing Machine Operators
data.def: Perform work involved in developing and processing photographic images from film or digital media. May perform precision tasks such as editing photographic negatives and prints.

data.title: Computer numerically controlled tool operators and programmers
data.soc_title: Computer Numerically Controlled Tool Operators and Programmers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Computer numerically controlled tool operators
data.def: Operate computer-controlled tools, machines, or robots to machine or process parts, tools, or other work pieces made of metal, plastic, wood, stone, or other materials. May also set up and maintain equipment.

data.title: Computer numerically controlled tool programmers
data.def: Develop programs to control machining or processing of materials by automatic machine tools, equipment, or systems. May also set up, operate, or maintain equipment.

data.title: Miscellaneous production workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Adhesive bonding machine operators and tenders
data.soc_title: Adhesive Bonding Machine Operators and Tenders
data.def: Operate or tend bonding machines that use adhesives to join items for further processing or to form a completed product. Processes include joining veneer sheets into plywood; gluing paper; or joining rubber and rubberized fabric parts, plastic, simulated leather, or other materials. Excludes “Shoe Machine Operators and Tenders” (51-6042).

data.title: Cleaning, washing, etc
data.soc_title: Cleaning, Washing, and Metal Pickling Equipment Operators and Tenders
data.def: Operate or tend machines to wash or clean products, such as barrels or kegs, glass items, tin plate, food, pulp, coal, plastic, or rubber, to remove impurities.

data.title: Cooling and freezing equipment operators and tenders
data.soc_title: Cooling and Freezing Equipment Operators and Tenders
data.def: Operate or tend equipment such as cooling and freezing units, refrigerators, batch freezers, and freezing tunnels, to cool or freeze products, food, blood plasma, and chemicals.

data.title: Etchers and engravers
data.def: Engrave or etch metal, wood, rubber, or other materials. Includes such workers as etcher-circuit processors, pantograph engravers, and silk screen etchers. Photoengravers are included in “Prepress Technicians and Workers” (51-5111).

data.title: Molders, shapers, etc
data.soc_title: Molders, Shapers, and Casters, Except Metal and Plastic
data.def: Mold, shape, form, cast, or carve products such as food products, figurines, tile, pipes, and candles consisting of clay, glass, plaster, concrete, stone, or combinations of materials.

data.title: Paper goods machine setters, operators, etc
data.soc_title: Paper Goods Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
data.def: Set up, operate, or tend paper goods machines that perform a variety of functions, such as converting, sawing, corrugating, banding, wrapping, boxing, stitching, forming, or sealing paper or paperboard sheets into products.

data.title: Tire builders
data.def: Operate machines to build tires.

data.title: Helpers--production workers
data.def: Help production workers by performing duties requiring less skill. Duties include supplying or holding materials or tools, and cleaning work area and equipment. Apprentice workers are classified in the appropriate production occupations (51-0000).

data.title: Production workers, all other
data.def: All production workers not listed separately. Excludes “Packers and Packagers, Hand” (53-7064).

data.title: Transportation and material moving jobs
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Supervisors of transportation and material moving workers
data.soc_title: Supervisors of Transportation and Material Moving Workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Aircraft cargo handling supervisors
data.def: Supervise and coordinate the activities of ground crew in the loading, unloading, securing, and staging of aircraft cargo or baggage. May determine the quantity and orientation of cargo and compute aircraft center of gravity. May accompany aircraft as member of flight crew and monitor and handle cargo in flight, and assist and brief passengers on safety and emergency procedures. Includes loadmasters.

data.title: First-line supervisors of transportation and material moving workers, except aircraft cargo handling supervisors
data.def: No job definition found.

data.title: Air transportation workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Aircraft pilots and flight engineers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Airline pilots, copilots, etc
data.soc_title: Airline Pilots, Copilots, and Flight Engineers
data.def: Pilot and navigate the flight of fixed-wing aircraft, usually on scheduled air carrier routes, for the transport of passengers and cargo. Requires Federal Air Transport certificate and rating for specific aircraft type used. Includes regional, national, and international airline pilots and flight instructors of airline pilots. Excludes “Electro-Mechanical and Mechatronics Technologists and Technicians” (17-3024).

data.title: Commercial pilots
data.def: Pilot and navigate the flight of fixed-wing aircraft on nonscheduled air carrier routes, or helicopters. Requires Commercial Pilot certificate. Includes charter pilots with similar certification, and air ambulance and air tour pilots. Excludes regional, national, and international airline pilots. Excludes “Electro-Mechanical and Mechatronics Technologists and Technicians” (17-3024).

data.title: Air traffic controllers and airfield operations specialists
data.soc_title: Air Traffic Controllers and Airfield Operations Specialists
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Air traffic controllers
data.def: Control air traffic on and within vicinity of airport, and movement of air traffic between altitude sectors and control centers, according to established procedures and policies. Authorize, regulate, and control commercial airline flights according to government or company regulations to expedite and ensure flight safety.

data.title: Airfield operations specialists
data.def: Ensure the safe takeoff and landing of commercial and military aircraft. Duties include coordination between air-traffic control and maintenance personnel, dispatching, using airfield landing and navigational aids, implementing airfield safety procedures, monitoring and maintaining flight records, and applying knowledge of weather information.

data.title: Flight attendants
data.def: Monitor safety of the aircraft cabin. Provide services to airline passengers, explain safety information, serve food and beverages, and respond to emergency incidents.

data.title: Motor vehicle operators
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Ambulance drivers and attendants, except emergency medical technicians
data.soc_title: Ambulance Drivers and Attendants, Except Emergency Medical Technicians
data.def: Drive ambulance or assist ambulance driver in transporting sick, injured, or convalescent persons. Assist in lifting patients.

data.title: Driver/sales workers and truck drivers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Driver/sales workers
data.def: Drive truck or other vehicle over established routes or within an established territory and sell or deliver goods, such as food products, including restaurant take-out items, or pick up or deliver items such as commercial laundry. May also take orders, collect payment, or stock merchandise at point of delivery. Excludes “Coin, Vending, and Amusement Machine Servicers and Repairers” (49-9091) and “Light Truck Drivers” (53-3033).

data.title: Heavy and tractor-trailer truck drivers
data.def: Drive a tractor-trailer combination or a truck with a capacity of at least 26,001 pounds Gross Vehicle Weight (GVW). May be required to unload truck. Requires commercial drivers’ license. Includes tow truck drivers. Excludes “Refuse and Recyclable Material Collectors” (53-7081).

data.title: Light truck drivers
data.def: Drive a light vehicle, such as a truck or van, with a capacity of less than 26,001 pounds Gross Vehicle Weight (GVW), primarily to pick up merchandise or packages from a distribution center and deliver. May load and unload vehicle. Excludes “Couriers and Messengers” (43-5021) and “Driver/Sales Workers” (53-3031).

data.title: Passenger vehicle drivers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Bus drivers, school
data.def: Drive a school bus to transport students. Ensure adherence to safety rules. May assist students in boarding or exiting.

data.title: Bus drivers, transit and intercity
data.def: Drive bus or motor coach, including regular route operations, charters, and private carriage. May assist passengers with baggage. May collect fares or tickets.

data.title: Shuttle drivers and chauffeurs
data.def: Drive a motor vehicle to transport passengers on a planned or scheduled basis. May collect a fare. Includes nonemergency medical transporters and hearse drivers. Excludes “Ambulance Drivers and Attendants, Except Emergency Medical Technicians” (53-3011) and “Taxi Drivers” (53-3054).

data.title: Taxi drivers
data.def: Drive a motor vehicle to transport passengers on an unplanned basis and charge a fare, usually based on a meter. Excludes “Shuttle Drivers and Chauffeurs” (53-3053).

data.title: Motor vehicle operators, all other
data.def: All motor vehicle operators not listed separately.

data.title: Rail transportation workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Locomotive engineers and operators
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Locomotive engineers
data.def: Drive electric, diesel-electric, steam, or gas-turbine-electric locomotives to transport passengers or freight. Interpret train orders, electronic or manual signals, and railroad rules and regulations. Excludes “Engineers” (17-2011 through 17-2199).

data.title: Rail yard engineers, dinkey operators, etc
data.soc_title: Rail Yard Engineers, Dinkey Operators, and Hostlers
data.def: Drive switching or other locomotive or dinkey engines within railroad yard, industrial plant, quarry, construction project, or similar location.

data.title: Railroad brake, signal, etc
data.soc_title: Railroad Brake, Signal, and Switch Operators and Locomotive Firers
data.def: Operate or monitor railroad track switches or locomotive instruments. May couple or uncouple rolling stock to make up or break up trains. Watch for and relay traffic signals. May inspect couplings, air hoses, journal boxes, and hand brakes. May watch for dragging equipment or obstacles on rights-of-way.

data.title: Railroad conductors and yardmasters
data.def: Coordinate activities of switch-engine crew within railroad yard, industrial plant, or similar location. Conductors coordinate activities of train crew on passenger or freight trains. Yardmasters review train schedules and switching orders and coordinate activities of workers engaged in railroad traffic operations, such as the makeup or breakup of trains and yard switching.

data.title: Subway and streetcar operators
data.def: Operate subway or elevated suburban trains with no separate locomotive, or electric-powered streetcar, to transport passengers. May handle fares.

data.title: Rail transportation workers, all other
data.def: All rail transportation workers not listed separately.

data.title: Water transportation workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Sailors and marine oilers
data.def: Stand watch to look for obstructions in path of vessel, measure water depth, turn wheel on bridge, or use emergency equipment as directed by captain, mate, or pilot. Break out, rig, overhaul, and store cargo-handling gear, stationary rigging, and running gear. Perform a variety of maintenance tasks to preserve the painted surface of the ship and to maintain line and ship equipment. Must hold government-issued certification and tankerman certification when working aboard liquid-carrying vessels. Includes able seamen and ordinary seamen.

data.title: Ship and boat captains and operators
data.soc_title: Ship and Boat Captains and Operators
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Captains, mates, etc
data.soc_title: Captains, Mates, and Pilots of Water Vessels
data.def: Command or supervise operations of ships and water vessels, such as tugboats and ferryboats. Required to hold license issued by U.S. Coast Guard. Excludes “Motorboat Operators” (53-5022).

data.title: Motorboat operators
data.def: Operate small motor-driven boats. May assist in navigational activities.

data.title: Ship engineers
data.def: Supervise and coordinate activities of crew engaged in operating and maintaining engines, boilers, deck machinery, and electrical, sanitary, and refrigeration equipment aboard ship. Excludes “Engineers” (17-2000).

data.title: Other transportation workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Bridge and lock tenders
data.def: Operate and tend bridges, canal locks, and lighthouses to permit marine passage on inland waterways, near shores, and at danger points in waterway passages. May supervise such operations. Includes drawbridge operators, lock operators, and slip bridge operators.

data.title: Parking attendants
data.def: Park vehicles or issue tickets for customers in a parking lot or garage. May park or tend vehicles in environments such as a car dealership or rental car facility. May collect fee.

data.title: Transportation service attendants
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Automotive and watercraft service attendants
data.def: Service automobiles, buses, trucks, boats, and other automotive or marine vehicles with fuel, lubricants, and accessories. Collect payment for services and supplies. May lubricate vehicle, change motor oil, refill antifreeze, or replace lights or other accessories, such as windshield wiper blades or fan belts. May repair or replace tires. Excludes “Cashiers” (41-2011).

data.title: Aircraft service attendants
data.def: Service aircraft with fuel. May de-ice aircraft, refill water and cooling agents, empty sewage tanks, service air and oxygen systems, or clean and polish exterior.

data.title: Traffic technicians
data.def: Conduct field studies to determine traffic volume, speed, effectiveness of signals, adequacy of lighting, and other factors influencing traffic conditions, under direction of traffic engineer.

data.title: Transportation inspectors
data.def: Inspect equipment or goods in connection with the safe transport of cargo or people. Includes rail transportation inspectors, such as freight inspectors, rail inspectors, and other inspectors of transportation vehicles not elsewhere classified. Excludes “Transportation Security Screeners” (33-9093).

data.title: Passenger attendants
data.def: Provide services to ensure the safety of passengers aboard ships, buses, trains, or within the station or terminal. Perform duties such as explaining the use of safety equipment, serving meals or beverages, or answering questions related to travel. Excludes “Baggage Porters and Bellhops” (39-6011) and “Flight Attendants” (53-2031).

data.title: Transportation workers, all other
data.def: All transportation workers not listed separately.

data.title: Material moving workers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Conveyor operators and tenders
data.def: Control or tend conveyors or conveyor systems that move materials or products to and from stockpiles, processing stations, departments, or vehicles. May control speed and routing of materials or products.

data.title: Crane and tower operators
data.def: Operate mechanical boom and cable or tower and cable equipment to lift and move materials, machines, or products in many directions.

data.title: Dredge operators
data.def: Operate dredge to remove sand, gravel, or other materials in order to excavate and maintain navigable channels in waterways.

data.title: Hoist and winch operators
data.def: Operate or tend hoists or winches to lift and pull loads using power-operated cable equipment. Excludes “Crane and Tower Operators” (53-7021).

data.title: Industrial truck and tractor operators
data.def: Operate industrial trucks or tractors equipped to move materials around a warehouse, storage yard, factory, construction site, or similar location. Excludes “Logging Equipment Operators” (45-4022).

data.title: Laborers and material movers
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Cleaners of vehicles and equipment
data.def: Wash or otherwise clean vehicles, machinery, and other equipment. Use such materials as water, cleaning agents, brushes, cloths, and hoses. Excludes “Janitors and Cleaners, Except Maids and Housekeeping Cleaners” (37-2011).

data.title: Laborers and freight, stock, etc
data.soc_title: Laborers and Freight, Stock, and Material Movers, Hand
data.def: Manually move freight, stock, luggage, or other materials, or perform other general labor. Includes all manual laborers not elsewhere classified. Excludes “Construction Laborers” (47-2061) and “Helpers, Construction Trades” (47-3011 through 47-3019). Excludes “Material Moving Workers” (53-7011 through 53-7199) who use power equipment.

data.title: Machine feeders and offbearers
data.def: Feed materials into or remove materials from machines or equipment that is automatic or tended by other workers.

data.title: Packers and packagers, hand
data.def: Pack or package by hand a wide variety of products and materials.

data.title: Stockers and order fillers
data.def: Receive, store, and issue merchandise, materials, equipment, and other items from stockroom, warehouse, or storage yard to fill shelves, racks, tables, or customers’ orders. May operate power equipment to fill orders. May mark prices on merchandise and set up sales displays. Excludes “Shipping, Receiving, and Inventory Clerks” (43-5071), “Laborers and Freight, Stock, and Material Movers, Hand” (53-7062), and “Packers and Packagers, Hand” (53-7064).

data.title: Pumping station operators
data.def: No definition found for this Summary Category.

data.title: Gas compressor and gas pumping station operators
data.soc_title: Gas Compressor and Gas Pumping Station Operators
data.def: Operate steam-, gas-, electric motor-, or internal combustion-engine driven compressors. Transmit, compress, or recover gases, such as butane, nitrogen, hydrogen, and natural gas.

data.title: Pump operators, except wellhead pumpers
data.def: Tend, control, or operate power-driven, stationary, or portable pumps and manifold systems to transfer gases, oil, other liquids, slurries, or powdered materials to and from various vessels and processes.

data.title: Wellhead pumpers
data.def: Operate power pumps and auxiliary equipment to produce flow of oil or gas from wells in oil field.

data.title: Refuse and recyclable material collectors
data.def: Collect and dump refuse or recyclable materials from containers into truck. May drive truck.

data.title: Tank car, truck, etc
data.soc_title: Tank Car, Truck, and Ship Loaders
data.def: Load and unload chemicals and bulk solids, such as coal, sand, and grain, into or from tank cars, trucks, or ships, using material moving equipment. May perform a variety of other tasks relating to shipment of products. May gauge or sample shipping tanks and test them for leaks.

data.title: Material moving workers, all other
data.def: All material moving workers not listed separately.
